<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17440728-7">
               <interp inst="t17440728-7" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17440728-7" type="year" value="1744"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17440728-7" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17440728"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17440728-7" type="date" value="17440728"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17440728-7-off39-c69" targOrder="Y" targets="t17440728-7-defend86 t17440728-7-off39 t17440728-7-verdict43"></join>
         
               <p>303. + 
               
                  <persName id="t17440728-7-defend86" type="defendantName">
                     James 
                     Everett 
                  <interp inst="t17440728-7-defend86" type="surname" value="Everett"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17440728-7-defend86" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17440728-7-defend86" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             , of <placeName id="t17440728-7-defloc38">St. Magnes the Martyr</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17440728-7-defloc38" type="placeName" value="St. Magnes the Martyr"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17440728-7-defloc38" type="type" value="defendantHome"></interp>
                  <join result="persNamePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17440728-7-defend86 t17440728-7-defloc38"></join> , was indicted for <rs id="t17440728-7-off39" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17440728-7-off39" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17440728-7-off39" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing a silk handkerchief, value 2 s. the goods of 
                     
                        <persName id="t17440728-7-victim88" type="victimName">
                           Isaac 
                           Tolke 
                        <interp inst="t17440728-7-victim88" type="surname" value="Tolke"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17440728-7-victim88" type="given" value="Isaac"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17440728-7-victim88" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17440728-7-off39 t17440728-7-victim88"></join>
                     </persName>
                      
                  , privately from his person
            </rs>, <rs id="t17440728-7-cd40" type="crimeDate">June 18</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17440728-7-off39 t17440728-7-cd40"></join>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17440728-7-person89">
                  Isaac 
                  Tolke 
               <interp inst="t17440728-7-person89" type="surname" value="Tolke"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17440728-7-person89" type="given" value="Isaac"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17440728-7-person89" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 18th of June coming through the <placeName id="t17440728-7-crimeloc41">Monument Yard</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17440728-7-crimeloc41" type="placeName" value="Monument Yard"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17440728-7-crimeloc41" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17440728-7-off39 t17440728-7-crimeloc41"></join>, I saw a company of women, and asked what those people were there for; they said they are the wives of those persons who are gone to Flanders ; while I was standing there I felt, as I thought, a hand at my breeches pocket*, I put my hand in this pocket and my handkerchief was gone; the Prisoner was just by me, his right hand was under his apron, and his left hand in his bosom. I had a suspicion of him, took his apron up, and he dropped the handkerchief down upon his feet; I took it up, took him by the arm, and carried him (I think) to the White Hart by Bishopsgate. I said if I could get a good character of him I would not prosecute him. I sent for his mother, and she said he was a vile <rs id="t17440728-7-deflabel42" type="occupation">boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17440728-7-defend86 t17440728-7-deflabel42"></join>, and behaved very undutifully, and had followed this practice these two years.</p>
               <p>*The Prosecutor found in the Prisoner's left hand near three pounds that he had taken out of his breeches pocket, but out of tenderness to him he would not lay that in the indictment.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. My father and mother-in-law were always vile people to me, or I should not have been drove to this way of living. <rs id="t17440728-7-verdict43" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17440728-7-verdict43" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17440728-7-verdict43" type="verdictSubcategory" value="theftunder1s"></interp>
               Guilty 10 d.
            </rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17440728-7-punish44" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17440728-7-punish44" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17440728-7-defend86 t17440728-7-punish44"></join>
               
                     <note>[Transportation. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
